# Async CNN

This project was made for a academic exercise, implementing asynchronous training for a convolutional neural network.

## Technologies

Python was the main tool here, using PyTorch for all the model development. The simulation was made with Docker, deploying each container as a worker of the distributed training system. 
For the use of GPUs Docker requires some extra installations, look at the binnacle notebook if you want to see the different decisions that were made along the process. 

